json string.message: As of 1.13, CustomName for entities and item display names (and lore in 1.14) started using JSON text components. They still need to be stored in a string, because NBT cannot store direct JSON. An example looks like this: `"{\"color\":\"blue\",\"text\":\"example\"}"`. If you don't care about colors and formatting and just want plain text, you can use this shortcut: `"\"example\""`

escaping.message: When you need a string to contain special characters that normally indicate special behavior for the parser, you need to escape those characters. For example, if you want to put `This is an "example" string` inside a string, you need to escape the quotes to tell the parser that those quotes are part of the string. You do that by preceding the character with a `\`: `"This is an \"example\" string"`

marker aec.message: The following area_effect_cloud won't have particles and will last ~6.8 years: ```/summon minecraft:area_effect_cloud ~ ~ ~ {Age:-2147483648,Duration:-1,WaitTime:-2147483648}```
